Task
Change the sign of the larger of two numbers
Write a function called changeMax that takes two numbers a and b as arguments, reverses the sign of the larger of the numbers, and returns that number. If the numbers are equal, return the message "The numbers are equal".
Example:
• the changeMax (9, 4) function must return -9;
• the changeMax (1, 6) function must return -6;
• the changeMax (0, 4) function must return -4;
• the changeMax (-1, -3) function must return 1;
• the changeMax (4, 4) function must return "The numbers are equal".

Solution
function changeMax (a, b) {
if (a === b) return "The numbers are equal";
else if (a <b) return -b;
else return -a;
}
